rComments: She somehow manages to make an interesting topic painfully boring. Lectures are not good, poorly organized. Lecture notes have 150+ slides, most of which are superfluous, so you end up searching through pages of garbage when trying to study. Avoid if possible.
teacherRatingTags: ['Group projects', 'Get ready to read', 'Graded by few things']

rComments: She's a nice person but her lectures focus too much on the theoretical aspect. As it was her 1st semester, I believe there's room for improvement. Most of the content can be and should be learnt via examples. YouTube, tutorials and labs will save your ass. Bulky project but graded fairly as long as it is relevant and you can explain how it works.

Her first semester & it shows. The midterm was exactly what was practised in tutorials & assignment was easy for 10% but the project was VERY time consuming, though she seemed to mark it very easily. Final was tough but no surprises. Lectures useless but you can do well in the course if you study off Youtube. Nice woman but all in all average prof
Honestly she was a good professor, the other reviewers might just not be cut out for CS if they're struggling with an introductory database class.

Professor Kantere is very unorganized and doesn't fairly grade students. The whole class was left helpless studying for the exam without her giving proper help. If you try and ask her a question she will never give you a good answer. Overall she is a poor professor and I wouldn't advise anyone to ever take a class of hers.

Her lectures were so bad and poorly delivered that after the second week, only about 20% of the class attended the lectures on average. There was little guidance on the material, the assignment and the project (which was very time consuming and time constrained), and she doesn't communicate anything about the midterm nor the final. Mediocre.
